// C2: Acting Components
instance PermanentMagnetSynchronousMotor : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Permanent magnet synchronous motor paired with cycloidal gear for precise rotational control (75 deg/s speed, ±90 deg range) with position, speed, and acceleration control capabilities. Implements structured control protocols via SysML state machines for deterministic behavior."
]

instance CycloidalGearbox : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Mechanical cycloidal gearbox integrated with permanent magnet synchronous motor to achieve high torque transmission and precision motion control within the MABI MAX 100 robot axis system."
]

instance SafetyBarrierSystem : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Physical safety barriers (safety cells) implemented to enforce operational constraints and prevent unauthorized access to the robot axis during high-precision machining operations."
]

// C3: Physical sensing components
instance JointAngleEncoder : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "High-resolution encoder measuring joint angles in real-time for motion tracking and friction analysis in the MABI MAX 100 robot axis system."
    DTDFVocab:producedData JointAngleDataTransmitted
]

instance TorqueSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Load cell-based torque sensor measuring rotational torque during machining operations to support joint friction identification and operational performance monitoring."
    DTDFVocab:producedData TorqueDataTransmitted
]

instance MotorCurrentSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Current sensor monitoring motor winding currents for electrical parameter analysis and indirect torque estimation in the robot axis system."
    DTDFVocab:producedData CurrentDataTransmitted
]

instance EnvironmentalTemperatureSensor : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Temperature sensor measuring operational environment conditions to account for thermal effects on joint friction and motor performance."
    DTDFVocab:producedData TemperatureDataTransmitted
]

// C4: Physical-to-virtual interaction
instance JointAngleDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom JointAngleEncoder
]

instance TorqueDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom TorqueSensor
]

instance CurrentDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom MotorCurrentSensor
]

instance TemperatureDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom EnvironmentalTemperatureSensor
]

// C10: Models/Data
instance SysMLArchitectureModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "SysML Internal Block Diagram (IBD) representing the functional architecture of the MABI MAX 100 robot axis including component hierarchy (motor, gearbox, encoders) and interface definitions for control system integration."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo MQTTEnabler
]

instance SimulinkBehavioralModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "MathWorks Simulink model simulating the dynamic behavior of the motor-gearbox system including friction compensation algorithms and motion prediction for joint friction identification."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SimulinkEnabler
]

instance AADLSafetyArchitecture : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "AADL architecture description for safety-critical components including component hierarchy, interface definitions, and property constraints for the robot axis safety system."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo AssetAdministrationShell
]

instance JointFrictionAnalysisModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Analytical model for joint friction characterization using aggregated sensor data traces to identify friction patterns and operational inefficiencies in the robot axis system."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo DataProcessingEnabler
]

instance JointAngleData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Real-time joint angle measurements transmitted via MQTT protocol for motion tracking and performance analysis in the digital twin system."
    DTDFVocab:fromData JointAngleDataTransmitted
]

instance TorqueData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Rotational torque measurements collected from load cells during machining operations for friction analysis and operational performance monitoring."
    DTDFVocab:fromData TorqueDataTransmitted
]

instance CurrentData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Motor winding current measurements used for electrical parameter analysis and indirect torque estimation in the robot axis system."
    DTDFVocab:fromData CurrentDataTransmitted
]

instance TemperatureData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Environmental temperature measurements accounting for thermal effects on joint friction and motor performance in the manufacturing environment."
    DTDFVocab:fromData TemperatureDataTransmitted
]

// C11: Enablers
instance MQTTEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "MQTT protocol implementation for low-latency, publish-subscribe telemetry data transmission from physical sensors to the digital twin system, enabling scalable real-time data streaming."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataAggregationService, ContextualDataTraceService
]

instance AssetAdministrationShell : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Industry 4.0 compliant Asset Administration Shell framework standardizing asset modeling and enabling semantic enrichment of sensor data for interoperability with other industrial systems."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataInteroperabilityService
]

instance SimulinkEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "MathWorks Simulink simulation environment enabling dynamic system modeling of the motor-gearbox system for friction compensation and motion prediction analysis."
    DTDFVocab:enables FrictionCompensationService
]

instance DataProcessingEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Modular data processing pipeline aggregating and abstracting sensor data traces for joint friction identification and operational performance analysis."
    DTDFVocab:enables JointFrictionIdentificationService, OperationalPerformanceMonitoringService
]

// C6: Services
instance DataAggregationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Real-time sensor data aggregation service collecting joint angle, torque, current, and temperature measurements for contextual data trace creation in the digital twin."
    DTDFVocab:provides ContextualDataTraceInsight
]

instance ContextualDataTraceService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service processing and abstracting raw sensor data into structured contextual data traces for downstream analysis and visualization."
    DTDFVocab:provides DataTraceInsight
]

instance JointFrictionIdentificationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service analyzing aggregated sensor data to identify joint friction patterns and operational inefficiencies in the robot axis system."
    DTDFVocab:provides FrictionAnalysisInsight
]

instance OperationalPerformanceMonitoringService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service monitoring operational performance metrics including motion accuracy and energy consumption based on processed sensor data traces."
    DTDFVocab:provides PerformanceMetricsInsight
]

instance DataInteroperabilityService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service ensuring semantic interoperability of digital twin data through standardized Asset Administration Shell framework for integration with other industrial systems."
    DTDFVocab:provides InteroperabilityInsight
]

instance FrictionCompensationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service implementing friction compensation algorithms in Simulink to predict and mitigate friction effects on robot axis motion performance."
    DTDFVocab:provides CompensationRecommendationAction
]

// C17: Insights/Actions
instance ContextualDataTraceInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Structured contextual data traces created from aggregated sensor measurements enabling temporal and spatial analysis of robot axis operations."
]

instance DataTraceInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Processed data traces representing operational patterns and anomalies detected in the robot axis system for diagnostic purposes."
]

instance FrictionAnalysisInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Identified joint friction patterns and operational inefficiencies derived from aggregated sensor data analysis for maintenance planning."
]

instance PerformanceMetricsInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Operational performance metrics including motion accuracy (±90 deg range) and energy consumption derived from processed sensor data for manufacturing optimization."
]

instance InteroperabilityInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Standardized data representation enabling seamless integration of the digital twin with other Industry 4.0 compliant manufacturing systems."
]

instance CompensationRecommendationAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Automated friction compensation recommendations generated by Simulink models to optimize robot axis motion performance."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

// C1: Environment
instance ManufacturingEnvironment : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:desc "High-precision industrial manufacturing environment hosting the MABI MAX 100 robot axis system with cyclic machining processes requiring real-time sensor data collection."
    base:contains PermanentMagnetSynchronousMotor, CycloidalGearbox, JointAngleEncoder, TorqueSensor, MotorCurrentSensor, EnvironmentalTemperatureSensor, SafetyBarrierSystem, RobotAxisSystem, DigitalShadowSystem
]

// C5: Components
instance RobotAxisSystem : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Physical robot axis system comprising motor, gearbox, encoders, and safety components enabling precise motion control for machining operations in the MABI MAX 100 industrial robot."
    base:isContainedIn ManufacturingEnvironment
]

instance DigitalShadowSystem : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Digital shadow implementation for the MABI MAX 100 robot axis providing passive monitoring services through real-time sensor data aggregation and contextual trace creation."
    base:isContainedIn ManufacturingEnvironment
]

instance twinning_time_scale : DTDFVocab:TimeScale [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system described in the provided documents does not explicitly detail synchronization frequencies, time scales for services, or latency requirements between physical and digital components. The text references **Model-Based Systems Engineering (MBSE)** methodologies such as **RFLP (Requirements, Functions, Logics, Physics)**, which abstract system modeling into hierarchical layers (requirements, functional, logical, and physical), but does not specify temporal alignment mechanisms, granularity (e.g., millisecond vs. second-level updates), or real-time constraints. The **Digital Shadow Reference Model** (Fig. 1) emphasizes a **one-way data flow** from physical objects to digital representations, implying passive data aggregation without explicit temporal synchronization protocols or latency thresholds. Thus, **no concrete temporal specifications** (e.g., update rates, synchronization protocols, or granularity) are provided in the documents."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system’s orchestration is framed within **Model-Based Systems Engineering (MBSE)** methodologies, utilizing **architecture description languages (ADLs)** such as **SysML (Internal Block Diagrams), AADL, and MontiArc** to model systems from a **component-connector perspective**. The **RFLP methodology** (Requirements, Functions, Logics, Physics) provides a **hierarchical abstraction framework** for structuring system models across layers. However, the document does not detail **runtime orchestration patterns**, **resource-aware coordination**, or **scalability mechanisms**. Instead, it emphasizes **static structural modeling** (e.g., component interfaces, interconnections) and **integration of heterogeneous tools** (e.g., Simulink for behavior) without addressing dynamic system-wide coordination or modular service-oriented designs."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "
The lifecycle of a Digital Twin (DT) system is structured through **Model-Based Systems Engineering (MBSE)** methodologies, which decompose system modeling into hierarchical abstraction layers: **requirements, functional architecture, logical architecture, and product/technical layers**. Transition management between these phases is facilitated by **architecture description languages (ADLs)** such as **ACME, AADL, MontiArc, or SysML Internal Block Diagrams (IBDs)**, which define component-connector perspectives, interfaces, and interconnections. Behavior modeling at the logical and product layers integrates **state machines (SysML v1.7), MontiArc Automaton, or simulation tools (e.g., MathWorks Simulink)** for detailed dynamic analysis. Lifecycle governance is implicitly addressed through **heterogeneous stakeholder integration** (per [31]), ensuring alignment across engineering disciplines, but explicit governance frameworks (e.g., ISO/IEC standards or CMMI) are not mentioned. The lifecycle evolves from **passive data aggregation (digital shadow phase)**—where data flows unidirectionally from physical assets to digital representations—to **active DT phases**, where processed insights are fed back into physical systems via **active software components** (per [32]–[37])."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "
The Digital Twin system emphasizes **model fidelity** through **multi-layered MBSE methodologies** (e.g., RFLP [18, 19], OOSEM [20], SPES [21], SMArDT [22]), which ensure hierarchical abstraction from requirements to physical layers. **Validation and verification (V&V)** methods are implied via:
- **Architecture description languages (ADLs)** (e.g., AADL [24], MontiArc [25, 26]) for structural consistency,
- **Behavioral modeling** (e.g., SysML state machines, Simulink simulations [28, 29, 30]) for dynamic validation,
- **Uncertainty quantification** via **data aggregation and abstraction** processes (as per Digital Shadow models [32]), though explicit error detection/correction mechanisms are not detailed.
Quality assurance processes are inferred from **heterogeneous stakeholder integration** [31] and **cross-tool consistency** (e.g., SysML + Simulink), ensuring traceability across modeling notations. However, **specific metrics for accuracy, precision, or uncertainty sources** (e.g., sensor noise, model bias) are not provided.
"
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "The technical network infrastructure for this Digital Twin system is described implicitly through the **MQTT protocol** as the primary communication channel for streaming data from physical to digital components. No explicit details are provided regarding network topology (e.g., mesh, star), bandwidth requirements, latency thresholds, or redundancy mechanisms. Security protocols are not mentioned, nor are specific communication protocols beyond MQTT (e.g., OPC UA, TCP/IP). The document does not elaborate on the underlying network architecture beyond its role in facilitating the **unidirectional data flow** defined for digital shadows."
]

instance horizontal_integration : DTDFVocab:HoriIntegration [
    base:desc "The document highlights the need for **integration of heterogeneous modeling tools** (e.g., SysML for architecture, Simulink for simulation, general-purpose languages like C++/Java for behavior) within a **Model-Based Systems Engineering (MBSE)** framework. It mentions the use of **architecture description languages (ADLs)** like SysML, AADL, and MontiArc to describe system components and connectors, but does not specify **data exchange protocols** (e.g., MQTT, OPC UA, RESTful APIs) or **interoperability standards** for external systems. The text does not reference **enterprise systems**, **PLM integration**, or **legacy system wrappers**, nor does it detail **Kafka-based event streaming** or **XMI-based model exchange**. Instead, it focuses on **tool-specific integration** (e.g., combining SysML with Simulink) without explicit horizontal integration patterns."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "
The document references **industry standards** indirectly through **MBSE methodologies** (e.g., **SysML [17], ACME [23], AADL [24]**) and **architecture description languages (ADLs)**, which are standardized frameworks for system modeling. **Interoperability** is implied via **heterogeneous tool integration** (MBSE tools + simulation engines + general-purpose code), but no specific **certification frameworks** (e.g., ISO/IEC 42010, IEEE 27001) or **compliance requirements** (e.g., GDPR for data traces) are mentioned. The **Digital Shadow Reference Model** (Fig. 1) aligns with **UML class diagrams**, suggesting adherence to **OMG standards**, but no explicit **DT-specific standards** (e.g., ISO/IEC 23247) are cited. **Compliance frameworks** are not detailed beyond the **methodological rigor** of MBSE and ADLs."
]

instance security_and_safety_considerations : DTDFVocab:SecuritySafety [
    base:desc "
The Digital Twin system incorporates **safety-critical mechanisms** through the **safety cell** of the robotic system (e.g., MABI robotic arm), which **restricts the maximum working range** to predefined boundaries, ensuring physical safety by preventing collisions or unauthorized access to hazardous zones. Data streaming for the Digital Twin is facilitated via **MQTT protocol**, which, while not explicitly detailing encryption or authentication, implies a need for secure communication channels in industrial automation contexts. No explicit mention of **OAuth 2.0, TLS 1.2+, ISO/IEC 27001, or fail-safe states via FMI** is present in the provided documents. The system’s safety is primarily governed by **physical containment** rather than digital security protocols or compliance frameworks."
]